</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="242" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1458,374,1084]" pageId="7" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,914,940]" pageId="7" pageNumber="242">Comments:—</emphasis>
Similar specimens occurred in several samples from each of 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1106,914,940]" name="Guam" pageId="7" pageNumber="242">Guam</collectingCountry>
and Yap but were always rare. There was considerable variation among these specimens and some clear differences, so I have chosen to define two species on the basis of ultrastructural details. For this species, defined on the specimen from Y45-5, I found no internal aspect but for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobban" authorityYear="2021" box="[384,523,1022,1048]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Ulnariaceae" genus="Divergita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Licmophorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="242" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[384,523,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="242">D. decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the internal view shows the characteristics of 
<taxonomicName box="[1033,1139,1023,1048]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Ulnariaceae" genus="Divergita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Licmophorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="242" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1139,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="242">Divergita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which do not vary between species.
</paragraph>
